<DOC><DOCNO> AP890916-0144 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-16-89 2246EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-RiverSpill     09-16 0219</FIRST><SECOND>AM-River Spill,0224</SECOND><HEAD>Fuel Spill Closes Part Of Hudson River</HEAD><DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A 30-mile stretch of the Hudson River wasclosed to water traffic Saturday after several thousand gallons ofoil was discovered spilled in the river, authorities said.   The river was closed from the Port of Albany to below Catskillafter a petroleum product believed to be a heavy fuel oil spilledinto the river late Friday night, according to officials from thestate Department of Environmental Conservation.   The actual spill _ which originated in the Port of Albany _ wasabout 20 miles long and extended from Albany to Coxsackie, saidCoast Guard officials from Governors Island in New York City.   The spill was reported early Saturday, said R.W. Groneman, adepartment spokesman. He said it wasn't known who made the call.   ``The type and amount of the oil as well as the source areunknown,'' said Petty Officer Jeff Crawley.   Groneman said the spill was toward the western shore of theriver. He said there was concern over wildlife and waterfowl in thearea.   ``The parties responsible for this hit and run environmentaldisaster will face stiff penalties,'' said Commissioner ThomasJorling of the environmental conservation department. ``They willalso get a bill from New York state for the cost of the cleanup.''</TEXT></DOC>